cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a differentiable framework for training multiple object trackers using deep learning. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically object tracking, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to optimizing the standard MOT metrics, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also involves robotics and motion tracking, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed framework on a benchmark dataset, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
